  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "VETERINARY NURSE / TECHNICIAN",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Job Description</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Conduct diagnostic tests, laboratory procedures, and radiographic imaging (X-rays) as required</p></li><li><p>Prepare animals, surgical instruments, and treatment areas for surgical and medical procedures</p></li><li><p>Administer medications, vaccinations, anaesthesia, and treatments under the supervision of a Veterinarian</p></li><li><p>Provide emergency first aid, inpatient nursing care, and post-operative monitoring</p></li><li><p>Observe, assess, and accurately report on animals’ behaviour, vital signs, and clinical condition</p></li><li><p>Safely restrain animals for examination, treatment, and diagnostic procedures</p></li><li><p>Assist veterinarians during consultations, surgeries, and medical procedures</p></li><li><p>Collect, document, and maintain accurate animal case histories and medical records</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with clinical protocols, hygiene standards, and workplace safety procedures</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Job Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Minimum <strong>Degree in Veterinary Medicine</strong></p></li><li><p>At least <strong>2 years of relevant working experience</strong> in a veterinary clinic, hospital, or related animal care setting</p></li><li><p>Able to work independently with minimal supervision, as well as collaboratively within a multidisciplinary team</p></li><li><p>Strong sense of responsibility, professionalism, and ethical conduct</p></li><li><p>Demonstrates a caring, calm, and positive disposition when handling animals and interacting with colleagues or clients</p></li><li><p>Maintains strict confidentiality of medical records and client information</p></li><li><p>Committed to continuous professional development and keeping up to date with veterinary best practices</p></li><li><p>Open-minded, adaptable, and willing to learn new techniques and protocols</p></li><li><p>Able to prioritise work based on <strong>clinical urgency, presenting cases, and emergency situations.</strong></p></li><li><p>Willing to work flexible hours when required to meet operational and emergency care needs</p></li></ul>",
